On Tuesday, May 17, 2005, at 03:44PM, Josh Gibbs <gibbsjj(-at-)gmail.com> wrote:

>I find that installing swivel foot valve adjuster screws really makes
>solid valve adjustments quick and easy.  Especially if you are going
>from stock adjuster screws that have lots of flat spots worn into
>them!

Another reason the last adjustment went so fast...having new stock screws is a huge time saver. When the screws are badly worn, they mushroom and go flat but on an angle. This angle makes adjustment very hard because a little turn of the screw closes/opens the gap more than it normally would.

